ranjo's, published The Enneagram (1988), which became the first widely available book on the system. Don Richard Riso, working independently, published Personality Types (1987) and later, with Russ Hudson, developed the Levels of Development framework, which describes how each type looks across a spectrum from healthy to average to unhealthy. The Riso-Hudson model, published most completely in The Wisdom of the Enneagram (1999), remains the most widely used framework today.\n[...]\nCore Fear: Being corrupt, evil, or defective Core Desire: To be good, to have integrity, to be balanced Passion: Anger (held internally as resentment) Virtue: Serenity Fixation: Resentment Holy Idea: Holy Perfection\n[...]\nCore Fear: Being unwanted, unloved, dispensable Core Desire: To be loved, needed, appreciated Passion: Pride (the belief that others need them more than they need others) Virtue: Humility Fixation: Flattery Holy Idea: Holy Freedom (Holy Will)\n[...]\nDeceit\n[...]\ns original system contains several interconnected \"enneagrams\" (mappings of nine qualities onto the nine points). Three of the most important are the Enneagram of Passions, the Enneagram of Virtues, and the Enneagram of Holy Ideas\n[...]\nHow Passions, Virtues, and Holy Ideas Relate The passion is the\n[...]\nIt operates in\n[...]\nIt is not the\n[...]\n| Type | Passion | Virtue | Fixation | Holy Idea |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 1 | Anger | Serenity | Resentment | Holy Perfection |\n| 2 | Pride | Humility | Flattery | Holy Freedom |\n| 3 | Deceit | Truthfulness | Vanity | Holy Hope |\n| 4 | Envy | Equanimity | Melancholy | Holy Origin |\n| 5 | Avarice | Non-Attachment | Stinginess | Holy Omniscience |\n| 6 | Fear | Courage | Cowardice | Holy Faith |\n| 7 | Gluttony | Sobriety | Planning | Holy Wisdom |\n| 8 | Lust | Innocence | Vengeance | Holy Truth |\n| 9 | Sloth | Right Action | Indolence | Holy Love |\n[...]\nThe 9 Enneagram types are: Type 1 (The Reformer), Type 2 (The Helper), Type 3 (The Achiever), Type 4 (The Individualist), Type 5 (The Investigator), Type 6 (The Loyalist), Type 7 (The Enthusiast), Type 8 (The Challenger), and Type 9 (The Peacemaker). Each type has a core fear, core desire, dominant passion, and a corresponding virtue that emerges through spiritual growth.\n[...]\nDon Richard R\n[...]\nSandra Maitri\n\n---\n\nTitle: Enneagram Vices and Virtues - Enneagram Explained\nURL: https://enneagramexplained.com/enneagram-vices-and-virtues/\nPublished: 2022-12-08T05:08:36.000Z\nAuthor: Enneagram Explained\nHighlights:\n### The Enneagram Virtues\n[...]\nThe Enneagram Virtues on the other hand are essentially the opposite of the Vices and are what we can strive for (through enneagram growth work) and reach when we release the grip of our Vice and our personality (remember your type is actually a coping system that you have created/learned…. it’s not actually you!)\n[...]\n## Enneagram Vices and Virtues\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 1: Anger to Serenity\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 2: Pride to Humility\n[...]\nRiso and Hudson referred to it as vainglory – the pride in one’s own virtue. Focusing on others needs and helping is a wonderfully good thing but you must beware of the trap of helping in hopes that others will see and be grateful for your service.\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 3: Deceit to Veracity\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 4: Envy to Equanimity\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 5: Avarice to Non-Attachment\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 6: Fear to Courage\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 7: Gluttony to Sobriety\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 8: Lust to Innocence\n[...]\n### Vice and Virtue for Type 9: Sloth to Right Action","_meta":{"searchTime":1527}}]}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_qebb1ijek9p3_2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: Enneagram Leadership Coaching & Assessment | iEQ9 — EnlightUs Coaching\nURL: https://www.enlightuscoaching.com/enneagram\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nAt EnlightUs Coaching, we use the iEQ9 Enneagram assessment—the most research-backed, business-focused Enneagram tool available.\n[...]\n(Team Report) Understand how your team's types interact\n[...]\nStep 3: Integration & Application (Ongoing) Apply Enneagram insights to your coaching work, team dynamics, and leadership development—turning self-awareness into strategic action.\n[...]\nStand-alone assessment + debrief ($450)\n[...]\nTeam assessment + workshop (custom pricing for leadership teams)\n[...]\nThe iEQ9 Team Report maps your team's collective dynamics—revealing:\n[...]\nHigh-growth companies scaling leadership capacity\n[...]\nTeam Enneagram Intensive: Half-day or full-day workshop integrating assessment, team mapping, and strategic application.\n[...]\nInvestment: Starting at $4,500 (includes assessments for 6-12 participants + facilitated workshop)\n[...]\nEspecially in roles where relational dynamics are sensitive — like bringing a new leader into a highly experienced, all-female team — the Enneagram gives us a deeper layer of understanding that no résumé or reference ever could. It’s helped us avoid costly\n[...]\nand, more\n[...]\n, build teams\n[...]\nYes. The iEQ9 Team Report is specifically designed for leadership teams, revealing collective dynamics, communication patterns, and strategic blind spots. We facilitate team workshops that integrate assessment insights with real-time team challenges.\n[...]\nYes. The Enneagram assessment and integration are included in all 3-month and 6-month executive coaching programs. It's also available as a stand-alone service.\n[...]\nHow much does the Enneagram assessment cost?\n[...]\nIndividual iEQ9 assessment with 90-minute professional debrief: $450. Team assessments with workshop facilitation start at $4,500 for 6-12 participants. The Enneagram assessment is also included in all 3-month and 6-month executive coaching programs at no additional cost.\n[...]\nThe iEQ9 has a 95% accuracy rate based on 13+ years of research and validation. Most free online Enneagram tests rely on self-typing and lack scientific validation. The iEQ9 is the only business-grade Enneagram assessment designed specifically for leadership development, with reports covering decision-making, team dynamics, and performance under pressure.\n[...]\nIndividual Assessment + Debrief: $450 Complete the iEQ9 and schedule a 90-minute debrief session to explore your results and develop an integration plan.\n[...]\nTeam Assessment + Workshop: Starting at $4,500 Comprehensive team dynamics mapping with facilitated workshop for 6-12 participants.\n[...]\nIntegrated with Coaching: Included Enneagram assessment is included in all executive coaching programs (3-month and 6-month engagements).\n\n---\n\nTitle: Enneagram Training Program for Teams\nURL: https://www.enneagrammba.com/enneagram-team-program\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nField Guide and start practicing today.\n[...]\nIt's recommended that each team in the Program host an in-person kick-off workshop to build excitement, get buy-in, and create a readiness to dive into the curriculum as well as a program finale onsite. At the end of the program having submitted all required assignments, each member of the team will receive a Certification of Completion.\n[...]\nEach teammate will have an opportunity to participate in an Enneagram Know Your Number session, a simple 360-Review assessment process, and a results review with an Enneagram MBA Certified Coach\n[...]\nDina is a certified Enneagram Coach and leads the clinical team at UF Health Florida Recovery Center.\n[...]\nDemetrius brings together self-awareness with practical and actionable steps to his work with teams in DEI, leadership development, and sustainable culture change. He specializes in using the Enneagram and other professional development tools, like the DiSC, inside the public sector with his firm, Trust Leadership Collective. Workshop attendees rave about his high-energy, interactive, and impactful training experiences.\n[...]\nAt Enneagram MBA we use the Awareness to Action methodology. It's a simple but extremely effective model for growth that tailored for the business world.\n[...]\nintention of Dream Team Academy™ is to use the Enneagram to help you and your team better understand each other and their unique strengths and preferences.\n[...]\nThe Dream Team Academy Series is customized to meet the size, budget, and goals of each client so the investment will vary. Typical investments from participating organizations in the 6-month program tend to range between $350 - $500 per team member per month, taking into account travel logistics, number of teammates, additional departments who are participating, needed assessments and individual sessions, printed materials, etc.\n[...]\n- In-depth Enneagram and peer-review assessment and 1:1 results reviews\n- Actionable exercises focused on re-training how you see yourself and how you show up for yourself and others\n- New lessons—a mix of audio, videos, text formats\n- Monthly facilitated group coaching calls with a community of like-minded managers.\n- 1:1 coaching sessions for each student\n- Certification of Completion\n[...]\nTeams who are facing specific challenges or already high-functioning teams looking to deepen their professional development and team collaboration will benefit from this experience.\n[...]\nLearn more about the Best-Boss-Ever School where they'll spend 4-months with other upcoming and first time managers learning how to use the Enneagram to lead with self-awareness, confidence, and emotional intelligence to get the best of of their teams.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Leadership Development - The Enneagram in Business\nURL: https://theenneagraminbusiness.com/professional-enneagram-services/leadership-development/\nPublished: 2024-05-07T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nLeadership Development - The Enneagram in Business\n[...]\n# Leadership Development\n[...]\nQ: Why do you use the Enneagram for your development as a leader? A: “When you get to my level, no one tells you the truth anymore. The Enneagram does!” (CEO, Fortune 50 company)\n[...]\nWhen leaders are asked “What is your leadership style?” they rarely have a clear answer. That’s because leading is something leaders do so naturally it’s like the air they breathe. However, the Enneagram can answer this important question because there are 9 different leadership styles, each a direct result of our Enneagram types. Beyond understanding their leadership styles and its impact, leaders also use the Enneagram to develop ‘hard skills,’ ‘soft skills,’ and everything in between.\n[...]\nThrough leadership development using the Enneagram, leaders at all levels strengthen their task and relationship leadership skills. They also achieve breakthroughs in the most important personal qualities that are often very hard to teach, including empathy, integrity, clarity, and humility.\n[...]\nYou get to choose from among these areas because we customize our programs according to your organization’s specific needs.\n[...]\n###### Team leadership\n[...]\n###### Strategy and business savvy\n[...]\n###### Leader as coach\n[...]\n###### Custom programs\n[...]\n#### Leadership Program Formats\n[...]\nAll leadership development programs can be done virtually, in person or a combination (hybrid) and are stimulating, engaging, and interactive, with a focus on increasing skills and sustained leadership growth. These can be done in large groups or smaller groups called Leadership Learning Communities\n[...]\nAll programs begin\n[...]\nYou get to choose which leadership application areas you want, as well as the amount of time allotted needed to accomplish your objectives.\n[...]\n#### Phase 3 | Individual Leadership Coaching\n[...]\nWe strongly recommend from three to six coaching sessions for each leader so they can explore their development in a confidential and results-focused environment. This is an optional, although important, part of our programs.\n[...]\nThese programs can be done with intact leadership teams or as leadership development programs with a cross-section of leaders from your organization. We offer programs as large group sessions, smaller groups of leadership learning communities that meet for three hours monthly, or a combination of both.\n[...]\n22 global survey\n[...]\nof global respondents\n[...]\nstrong benefit of using\n[...]\nAs you can see\n[...]\nWe offer a public Train-the-Trainer certificate program, “Build Wise, Talented and Humble Leaders with the Enneagram” based on What Type of Leader Are You?. Details here.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Professional Team Training — Enneagram Tools By Sarah Robinson\nURL: https://www.enneagramtools.com/team-training\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n### Improve your team’s communication and self-awareness skills with the Enneagram Enhanced Team™ Training\n[...]\nThe Enneagram is a powerful model that gives a framework for everyone in the workplace to be valued for who they are without shame or exclusion. Every team that I have worked with that has used the Enneagram Enhanced Team training has improved and seen changes soon thereafter, sometimes right away (and they scheduled more sessions).\n[...]\n. I’m in\n[...]\n### The Enneagram Enhanced Team™ Training is a non-threatening way to make everyone feel important and build crucial self-awareness skills in your work team\n[...]\nDigital workbook for every person attending (printed materials available for additional cost)\n[...]\n## On-Site or Virtual Team Trainings\n[...]\nFor in-person trainings, I can join you at a local Austin location or travel to you anywhere in the US for additional cost. All trainings are provided a set of virtual materials, with the option to add-on printed materials. Before the training, we will meet to discuss your team’s needs and goals, create a personalized program and schedule, and make any adjustments needed to highlight your group’s ideal learning style and needs.\n[...]\nTrainings are offered in half-day, full-day, or multiple days. A half-day training will only cover the basics of the model and an overview of the types. A full-day training can start to get more specific to the people on the team. I highly recommend scheduling at least 2 full-day trainings so that everyone participating can feel confident about the basics of the model, learn more details about their specific type, and the group as a whole can explore the team dynamics.\n[...]\nHalf-day training starts at $1500 for a group of 2-10 participants. Full-day trainings start at $3000 and can be customized to your team's needs. Please inquire for a quote of a multi-day training and include any special team needs or travel details.\n[...]\nOn-site trainings are always more dynamic and seem to have the strongest impact on the participants. Virtual meetings are sometimes the most effective way to bring a team together, but it is important to make sure that the team is not expected to multi-task during the call and is willing to be on camera and interactive in conversations. On-site trainings in the Austin area are quoted at the same price as virtual trainings. Outside that radius, travel costs will be added to the training total.\n[...]\n#### How do I know if this will make sense for my business?\n[...]\nPlease reach out for a free consultation about your business needs and let’s make a customized plan to integrate the Enneagram into your work or team.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Team Collaboration Powered by the Enneagram — LevelUp EQ\nURL: https://www.levelupeq.com/enneagramcoaching\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n#### Facilitated by MCC, ICF, and Enneagram-Certified Coaches.\n[...]\n#### $3500 for 3-10 Team Members.\n[...]\nIn our team coaching programs, we prioritize results, effective communication, heightened productivity, creative stimulation, and the overall professional growth of the team. Our ICF certified coaches are equipped with a deep understanding of business dynamics and Enneagram proficiency.\n[...]\nTeam coaching with our Enneagram-certified coaches starts at $3,500 for a two-hour virtual development session with up to 10 participant for a limited time. This includes:\n[...]\n#### A 2-hour remote-based experience with a certified Enneagram coach.\n[...]\n#### Reports to understand your team’s Enneagram style with our Team Enneagram results reporting.\n[...]\n#### Learning the team’s needs and\n[...]\nteaming outcomes via a 6\n[...]\n-minute Client Intake Session.\n[...]\n#### Understanding of each team member’s personality tendencies with Enneagram assessments and confidential results reporting.\n[...]\nBy utilizing the Enneagram, leaders gain valuable insights into what motivates, challenges, and drives productivity for each individual on their team. This awareness allows for tailored approaches to communication, task delegation, and overall team management.\n[...]\n#### Our Enneagram Program is your powerful path to better teaming and higher success. With our Certified Coaches, Tailored Coaching Approach, and Proven Measurable Results, you can propel your organization to new heights.\n[...]\n#### In the realm of organizational success, cohesive teams are pivotal. Teams that collaborate seamlessly, trust each other, communicate effectively, and navigate complex issues together are essential for reaching the organization's goals. The Enneagram serves as a transformative tool, providing a profound understanding of individual and team dynamics. This insight, when integrated into team coaching with Level Up EQ, facilitates the development of success-oriented teams. These teams, in turn, drive enhanced productivity and success, becoming the backbone of organizational growth and achievement.\n[...]\n#### Throughout the facilitated program, Level Up EQ coaches incorporate emotional intelligence training, accountability strategies, and feedback sessions that allow for trackable, measurable improvement and change. Ready to take the next step? Reach out to us for a complimentary 30-minute consultation. Let's chat about where you currently stand, where you aspire to be, and how Level Up EQ, combined with the power of the Enneagram, can be your ideal partner on this transformative journey.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Enneagram Coaching for Senior Leaders and Teams\nURL: https://workinvigorated.com/enneagram-coaching/\nPublished: 2025-08-02T16:03:47.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe Enneagram is a cornerstone of our coaching philosophy for business and secondary education leaders. We believe that skilled Enneagram coaching is the most powerful catalyst for individuals seeking profound professional and personal growth, and for organizations committed to building high-performing, engaged, cohesive teams.\n[...]\nAs a certified Enneagram coach with a background in business consulting, Kimberly brings more than insight – she brings precision. She uses the Enneagram not just as a self-awareness tool, but as a strategic lens to uncover patterns that shape how leaders think, communicate and lead. Her work helps individuals and teams break through plateaus, navigate conflict, and lead with greater clarity, courage and impact.\n[...]\nShe is an experienced Enneagram assessment and coaching professional, certified as an iEQ9 Integrative Enneagram Practitioner, Levels 1 and 2.\n[...]\nLevel 1 certification focuses on a deep understanding of the Enneagram for individual growth, equipping certified coaches to expertly interpret the iEQ9 professional reports and provide powerful one-on-one coaching. Coaches learn to debrief clients on their core type, subtypes and turn insights into a unique development path to unlock profound growth.\n[...]\nBuilding on Level 1, the Level 2 certification centers on TEAM and group dynamics, training Level 2 coaches to interpret iEQ9 Team Reports and facilitate workshops. Those certified at this level have developed the skills to apply the Enneagram in complex organizational settings, improving team cohesion, communication and overall performance.\n[...]\nTeams that work well together outperform those who don’t. For work groups, the benefits of working with the Enneagram as a cohort include:\n[...]\n- Understanding what motivates each team member and collective dynamics of your team\n- Improving each team member’s ability to work with others\n- Making individual differences a team strength\n- Having more empathy for fellow team members\n- Learning how to build a happier, healthier, high-performing team\n[...]\nYes! Our team Enneagram coaching and Enneagram workshops are popular and powerful! Reach out for details and to book a workshop program for your employees or leadership cohort.\n[...]\n“I had the privilege of working with Kimberly Harris through a\n[...]\ncoaching program, and the experience was insightful, impactful, and truly\n[...]\nboth personally and professionally. Kimberly is approachable\n[...]\nand a 36\n[...]\nassessment, she helped me better understand my\n[...]\nand purpose. I would strongly recommend Kimberly as a coach to leaders who are\n[...]\nto taking their leadership to the next level with greater self-awareness"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a88ea885-1950-40b9-b15d-36f548aa1b64","uuid":"b9743f2a-32d7-42e4-aa6a-5e59bff79f8e","timestamp":"2026-06-10T16:54:32.544Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: Enneagram Leadership Coaching & Assessment | iEQ9 — EnlightUs Coaching\nURL: https://www.enlightuscoaching.com/enneagram\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nAt EnlightUs Coaching, we use the iEQ9 Enneagram assessment—the most 